    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_UsersInRoles_GetRolesForUser",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve the roles associated with a specific user within a given application. It operates within the context of a Microsoft SQL Server database, typically part of an ASP.NET membership schema. The procedure takes an application name and a username as input, identifies the corresponding application and user IDs, and then fetches the roles assigned to that user within the specified application."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including querying multiple tables and handling potential null values, which adds a moderate level of complexity. The use of conditional logic to handle cases where the application or user does not exist also contributes to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@ApplicationName",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " (nvarchar(256)): This parameter specifies the name of the application for which the user's roles are to be retrieved. It is case-insensitive due to the use of the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "LOWER",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@UserName",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " (nvarchar(256)): This parameter specifies the username whose roles are to be retrieved. It is also case-insensitive."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
